description:
Bird's-eye Speedwell or Persian Speedwell (Veronica persica), photographed at Lakewood Park in Sunnyvale, CA.  Identified as belonging to the genus Veronica on the basis of the following (per Jepson's):

1) Whorled leaves.
2) Stamens 2.
3) Cauline leaves, sessile to short-petioled.
4) Corolla more or less radial, 4-lobed,sepals 5.

Identified as Veronica persica based on the following:

1) Racemes terminal; herbage generally hairy.
2) Plant an annual.
3) Pedicel subtending flower 15-30 mm long, generally > calyx.
4) Leaves crenate to serrate.

References:
1) Jepson's eFlora, "Key to Plantaginaceae."  Retrieved from http://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?key=220 on 3/26/18.
2) Jepson's eFlora, "Key to Veronica."  Retrieved from http://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/eflora/eflora_display.php?tid=11413 on 3/26/18.
3) Jepson's eFlora, "Veronica persica."  Retrieved from http://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/eflora/eflora_display.php?tid=47976
4) Wikipedia, "Veronica persica."  Retrieved from https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veronica_persica on 3/26/18.
